Mogri is not claimed here as a standard AI/ML literature term. It is a user-coined project term from the lumixdeee/mogri repo.

Source:
https://github.com/lumixdeee/mogri/tree/main/spec

Working meaning:
Mogri = the unknowns that matter.

AI harness meaning:
Mogri = the minimal container that preserves object, intent, constraints, and mattering unknowns across prompt/session/tool transformations. Without it, the system may drift, swap the task, lose invariants, or optimise a proxy.

So the right classification is:
"user-defined framework term with public source material, not mainstream AI jargon."

The wrong classification is:
"hallucinated term that does not exist."
